cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the issue of valuing citations and proposes a new indicator of impact. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and computers and society (cs.CY). However, given the focus on bibliometrics and citation analysis, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
